org.dataconservancy.packaging.tool.api.generator

Interface PackageAssembler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BagItPackageAssembler

    public interface PackageAssembler
    Assembles some packaging model into physical form.

    The package assembler allows for the creation of named resources within a logical package, and the ultimate assembly of these resources into a final, physical packaged form.

      • reserveResource

        URI reserveResource(String path,
                    PackageResourceType type)
        Reserve (create a name, and potentially storage location for) a resource.

        Given a path and resource type, this method reserves a resource name (URI) for future population of content via putResource(URI, InputStream). The package content is assumed to be empty (0 bytes) until content is provided.

        z

        Note: This operation is optional. If an assembler does not support reserving URIs and updating content, then it shall throw and UnsupportedOperationException

        Parameters:
        path - Logical file path (including filename) of the resource relative to the package.
        type - Resource type (e.g. data, metadata, etc).
        Returns:
        URI of reserved resource

      • putResource

        void putResource(URI uri,
                 InputStream content)
        Commit new content to a previously created or reserved resource.

        Using a URI obtained from previously reserving a resource (via reserveResource(String, PackageResourceType)), this allows the content of the resource named by the URI to be set.

        Use of URIs not obtained through reserveResource(String, PackageResourceType) is undefined.

        Note: This operation is optional. If an assembler does not support reserving URIs and updating content, then it shall throw and UnsupportedOperationException

        Parameters:
        uri - URI naming the resource whose content is to be set.
        content - InputStream containing the content of the resource.

      • createResource

        URI createResource(String path,
                   PackageResourceType type,
                   InputStream content)
        Create a new resource in the package.

        Given a relative file path and some content, this method will add the content to the package, and return a URI that names it.

        Parameters:
        path - Logical file path (including filename) of the resource relative to the package.
        type - Resource type (e.g. data, metadata, etc).
        content - InputStream containing the content of the resource.
        Returns:
        URI of created resource

      • assemblePackage

        Package assemblePackage()
        Produce a Package object based on the added resources.

        Package's content is assembled from all previously created resources into final physical packaging form contained in an InputStream.

        Package's contentType is set based on the archiving and compression algorithms applied on the content.

        Package's name is set based on the input parameter "package-name".

        Note: Invoking this method more than once is undefined. It can be assumed that this method may imply some sort of finalization or cleanup of resources used in building the package.

        Returns:
        a Package

      • addParameter

        void addParameter(String key,
                  String value)
        Add a parameter to configure assembler information after initialization. Useful for times when a parameter may not be available until work is done later, but is needed prior to calling assemblePackage, such as putting information into an information file that isn't determined until the data files are written.
        Parameters:
        key - The name of the parameter to add
        value - The value of the parameter to add
